Thanks for the detailed report!

This is a known WinUI 3 platform limitation — `SwapChainPanel` (which backs `SKGLView` via ANGLE) does not support per-pixel transparency in WinUI 3. You can see this is already documented in our code. The WinUI team has had a long-standing request for this feature: https://github.com/microsoft/microsoft-ui-xaml/issues/5025

**Workaround:** Use `SKCanvasView` instead of `SKGLView` on Windows. `SKCanvasView` uses a different rendering path that does support transparency, though without GPU acceleration:

```csharp
// Option 1: Use SKCanvasView on all platforms
// <skia:SKCanvasView ... BackgroundColor="Transparent" />

// Option 2: Platform-specific handler to use SKGLView on mobile and SKCanvasView on Windows
```

A proper fix would require a new Direct3D composition-based view for WinUI 3. This is on our radar — see the work being done in #2817 and #2823.
